September 13, 2018

Slides: https://github.com/NHS-NSS-transforming-publications/uRos2018

Background

  • The Information Services Division (ISD) of NHS Scotland has a long history of producing official and national statistics.
  • We produce around 200 publications each year.
  • Traditional publication format is a static pdf document with accompanying excel tables.
  • Production uses proprietary software and is time-consuming, involving extensive manual formatting and checking.

Vision

Initial User Engagament

  • Focus groups and interviews with over 10 different user groups.
  • Determined user experiences of existing product and how the new product deisgn could meet their needs.
  • Created user stories which influenced the features of the minimum viable product.

Minimum Viable Product

  • Acute Hospital Activity and Beds publication released in December 2017.

MVP: Data explorer

Acute Activity data explorer R Shiny code

User Feedback and Testing

The Challenge of Scaling

  • R knowledge:
    • R training at an organisation level
    • R Style Guide
    • Blank R Project and R Shiny templates
    • Resources
  • Consistency:
    • Share [R Shiny code] for the original data explorer (https://github.com/Health-SocialCare-Scotland/Hospital-Acute-Activity/tree/master/Data-Explorer)
    • Next step: design manual

Next Steps

  • Psychiatric Hospital Activity publication to be released 25 September 2018.
  • Thematic approach to publications.
  • Re-design of Data quality page.
  • Automate production process (Reproducible Analytical Pipeline).
